(gen_random_uuid(), 'CCSS', 'HS', 'Mathematics', 'HSS.CP.A.1', 'Describe events as subsets of a sample space (the set of outcomes) using characteristics (or categories) of the outcomes, or as unions, intersections, or complements of other events ("or," "and," "not").', 'Statistics & Probability', 'Common Core State Standards', true, true, '2010'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'CCSS', 'HS', 'Mathematics', 'HSS.CP.A.2', 'Understand that two events A and B are independent if the probability of A and B occurring together is the product of their probabilities, and use this characterization to determine if they are independent.', 'Statistics & Probability', 'Common Core State Standards', true, true, '2010'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'CCSS', 'HS', 'Mathematics', 'HSS.CP.A.3', 'Understand the conditional probability of A given B as P(A and B)/P(B), and interpret independence of A and B as saying that the conditional probability of A given B is the same as the probability of A, and the conditional probability of B given A is the same as the probability of B.', 'Statistics & Probability', 'Common Core State Standards', true, true, '2010'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'CCSS', 'HS', 'Mathematics', 'HSS.CP.A.4', 'Construct and interpret two-way frequency tables of data when two categories are associated with each object being classified. Use the two-way table as a sample space to decide if events are independent and to approximate conditional probabilities.', 'Statistics & Probability', 'Common Core State Standards', true, true, '2010'),
